channel.title: Replaceing Models on server?
channel.description:
Alright so lately i've been putting a lot of models on my server. But i asked a friend who is good with models and said to not mess up old ones in the server. and said use 13,000+? so i did i used like 13,800 and everything was working fine. but then i go check the KBD and there are my GS shards all over my lava?
luckly i have a backup file, but what the hell do i replace? can any one give me a few numbers??? that arent goona be messing up my server please
thanks :l

item.title: Replaceing Models on server?
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

Michaelmmm:

what are some “useless ones” such as models like in the elf land or something that i can replce and no one goes there??

Search through the cache with the RSMV, and determine whether the model is useless or not.

item.title: Replaceing Models on server?
item.dc:creator: @Michaelmmm Michaelmmm
item.description:
@Michaelmmm wrote:

no dude thats not what i ment. for the “ITEMS” i replaced stupid stuff like goats horn and ect…

i’m talking about object models, like for ex: if i have 2 gzipped models and i wanna use 13800, 13801.

so i do, add model 13800,13801 but then when i log onto the server i see the lava filled with my gs shards wdf??

what are some “useless ones” such as models like in the elf land or something that i can replce and no one goes there??

It doesnt matter, all private servers are to sucky to use every single model.
